---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Torrance Watch: editorial independence, methodology, and how to verify our work.">
  <div class="page">
    <div class="kicker">About</div>
    <h1>About Torrance Watch</h1>
    <div class="dek">
      Torrance Watch is a standing, nonpartisan civic reference for the City of
      Torrance. We exist because local civic information is hard to find. Commercial
      news coverage has thinned. Official city communications are useful but not
      independent. Campaign materials are partisan by design. What's missing is a
      reliable place for Torrance residents to get oriented.
    </div>
    <div class="source">
      We launched in April 2026 with coverage of the June 2 municipal election. We
      continue after the election as a year-round reference for who holds office, how
      the city works, and what's being decided.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-head">What we do</div>
      <div class="section-sub">
        Publish sourced, nonpartisan information about elections, candidates, campaign
        finance, and city government. Equal treatment of every candidate in every race.
        Same depth. Same tone. Same format.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-head">What we don't do</div>
      <div class="section-sub">
        Endorse candidates. Accept campaign contributions. Coordinate with any campaign
        or political committee. Editorialize about motives or character. Publish
        anonymous claims.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-head">How to verify us</div>
      <div class="section-sub">
        Every factual claim on this site links to a public source. Campaign finance data
        comes directly from filings with the City of Torrance via NetFile. Candidate
        information comes from public records, official filings, ballot statements, and
        the candidates' own public statements. When we're uncertain about something, we
        say so.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-head">Editorial team</div>
      <div class="section-sub">
        Torrance Watch is operated by volunteer Torrance residents. The editorial team is
        pseudonymous during the 2026 election cycle to keep the focus on the work rather
        than on individuals. Contact:
        <a href="mailto:hello@torrancewatch.org" style="color:#A32D2D;">hello@torrancewatch.org</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-head">Corrections</div>
      <div class="section-sub" style="margin-bottom:0;">
        If you spot an error, email
        <a href="mailto:corrections@torrancewatch.org" style="color:#A32D2D;">corrections@torrancewatch.org</a>
        with the URL, the claim, and the correct information. We'll investigate, correct
        if needed, and note the correction publicly.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
